  <body><![CDATA[Great review, Patrick. I was trying to differentiate the reviews. Many of them seemed to be angry at a "follow your bliss" premise (which is often misunderstood), rather than critiquing the book itself. From your review (literal treasure - really?), I'm convinced that the book probably went off the rails in both directions. Shame. Fiction has enormous potential to illustrate that the 'bliss' referred to by great teachers has nothing to do with princes, places or porches... or treasures in the dessert. I'll skip it, and keep looking for New Thought fiction I can actually recommend. Thanks for your help with that.]]></body>
  
