  <body><![CDATA[Patrick, I really wonder what's your opinion about the book after another 8 years have passed. From my perspective I think that you were just behind the book's message a couple of years in your own life, that you just didn't experience yourself the second half of the story. And I think you highly oversimplified the message. The treasure at the end was not important at all, it was just a fulfillment, but the real treasures Santiago found on his way there. But as unrest souls cannot be tamed without pursuing their destinies, Santiago must have done everything he did up to the very end, so he could live his life with Fatima without wondering "what if". Don't you wonder yourself "what if"?]]></body>
  
